<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="17" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,152,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[196,318,301,327]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the only specimen in Reitter’s collection fitting the original description of the species. 
<collectingCountry box="[151,184,338,364]" name="American Samoa" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">As</collectingCountry>
seen below under 
<taxonomicName box="[404,578,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplirostris">
<emphasis box="[404,578,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. amplirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, this is the opposite sex of the 
<typeStatus box="[943,993,338,364]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1033,1206,338,363]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amplirostris">
<emphasis box="[1033,1206,338,363]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">L. amplirostris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is a female. They share the same locality of “Akbes” in 
<collectingCountry box="[667,753,376,402]" name="Turkey" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Turkey</collectingCountry>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Petri" box="[764,918,376,402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="21" refString="Petri, K. (1904 a) Beschreibung einiger neuer Lixus - arten. Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 23 (3 - 4): 65 - 77." type="journal article" year="1904" yearSuffix="a">
Petri (
<number box="[836,897,376,402]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1904.0">1904</number>
a)
</bibRefCitation>
described the gender difference as different species. Designation of a new synonymy is necessary: 
<taxonomicName authority="Boheman, 1842" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1842" box="[874,1318,413,439]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegantulus">
<emphasis box="[874,1104,413,438]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus elegantulus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Boheman" box="[1114,1318,413,439]" pageId="16" pageNumber="20" refString="Boheman, C. H. (1842) In Schoenherr C. J. [1842]. Genera et species curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Species novae aut hactenus minus cognitae, descriptionibus a Dom. L. Gyllenhal, C. H. Boheman, O. J. Fahraeus, et entomologis aliis illustratae. Tomus septimus. Pars prima. Supplementum continens. Roret, Paris; Fleischer, Lipsiae, [II] + 1 - 479 pp." type="journal article" year="1842">
Boheman, 
<number box="[1254,1318,413,439]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1842.0">1842</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Petri, 1904" authorityName="Petri" authorityYear="1904" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Lixus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="convexicollis" status="syn. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Lixus convexicollis</emphasis>
Petri, 
<number box="[381,440,450,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" value="1904.0">1904</number>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[447,528,450,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[447,528,450,476]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">syn. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
].
</paragraph>
